TITLE: Injecting IMessageBus into Wolverine Handlers via Method Argument in C#
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the recommended approach for obtaining an `IMessageBus` instance within a Wolverine message handler by injecting it directly as a method parameter. This keeps the handler method self-contained regarding its dependencies for message publishing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/wolverine/blob/main/docs/tutorials/best-practices.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
public static async Task HandleAsync(MyMessage message, IMessageBus messageBus)
{
    // handle the message..;
}
```

