TITLE: Order Creation via Minimal API with Marten Outbox Integration - C#
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates a Minimal API route in ASP.NET Core that processes POST requests, creates a new Order, stores it with Marten, and registers an OrderCreated message with Wolverine's outbox for deferred publishing. Dependencies must include Marten, Wolverine, and Minimal API support. The handler receives a CreateOrder command and required services, ensuring outbound message reliability by coupling publishing to transaction success.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/wolverine/blob/main/docs/guide/durability/marten/outbox.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
app.MapPost("/orders/create3", async (CreateOrder command, IDocumentSession session, IMartenOutbox outbox) =>
{
    var order = new Order
    {
        Description = command.Description
    };

    // Register the new document with Marten
    session.Store(order);

    // Don't worry, this message doesn't go out until
    // after the Marten transaction succeeds
    await outbox.PublishAsync(new OrderCreated(order.Id));

    // Commit the Marten transaction
    await session.SaveChangesAsync();
});
```

