TITLE: Implementing Conventional Wolverine Middleware with Stopwatch (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This C# snippet defines a `StopwatchMiddleware` class demonstrating Wolverine's conventional middleware approach. The `Before` method starts a `Stopwatch` instance stored in a field. The `Finally` method, which Wolverine places in a `finally` block during code generation, stops the stopwatch and logs the execution duration along with message envelope details using `ILogger` and `Envelope` parameters provided by Wolverine.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/wolverine/blob/main/docs/guide/handlers/middleware.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
public class StopwatchMiddleware
{
    private readonly Stopwatch _stopwatch = new();

    public void Before()
    {
        _stopwatch.Start();
    }

    public void Finally(ILogger logger, Envelope envelope)
    {
        _stopwatch.Stop();
        logger.LogDebug("Envelope {Id} / {MessageType} ran in {Duration} milliseconds",
            envelope.Id, envelope.MessageType, _stopwatch.ElapsedMilliseconds);
    }
}
```

