TITLE: Implementing a Custom Fluent Validation Failure Action in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to customize the behavior when Fluent Validation fails. It defines a custom exception class `MySpecialException` and a generic class `CustomFailureAction<T>` that implements the `Wolverine.FluentValidation.IFailureAction<T>` interface. The `Throw` method in `CustomFailureAction<T>` receives the message and validation failures, and throws the custom exception with a formatted error message.
