TITLE: Defining a Reservation Saga Class using Wolverine (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a Reservation saga by subclassing Saga in C#. It handles reservation booking and timeout events through dedicated handler methods that log actions and mark the saga as completed, triggering persistence changes. Dependencies include ILogger<Reservation> for logging and types BookReservation and ReservationTimeout for saga messages. Inputs are message objects; outputs are side-effects on the saga state and logs.
