TITLE: Routing Cascading Messages to Specific Endpoints in Wolverine (C#)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to send cascading messages to specific, named endpoints or URI destinations instead of relying on default routing rules. The handler returns an `IEnumerable<object>`, yielding messages (`GoNorth`, `GoWest`) modified with `ToEndpoint()` or `ToDestination()` extension methods to specify their target queues.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/wolverine/blob/main/docs/guide/handlers/cascading.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
// snippet: sample_ManuallyRoutedResponseHandler
public class ManuallyRoutedResponseHandler
{
    public IEnumerable<object> Consume(MyMessage message)
    {
        // Go North now at the "important" queue
        yield return new GoNorth().ToEndpoint("important");

        // Go West in a lower priority queue
        yield return new GoWest().ToDestination(new Uri("rabbitmq://queue/low"));
    }
}
// endSnippet
```

