TITLE: Executing Wolverine Environment Checks via Command Line using Bash
DESCRIPTION: This Bash command utilizes Oakton's environment check facility to verify the application's ability to connect to external infrastructure like databases and message brokers, as well as internal configuration validity. Running `dotnet run -- check-env` executes these checks and reports success or failure, aiding in diagnosing configuration or connectivity problems. It can also be used during startup to halt execution on failure.
