TITLE: Configuring Amazon SQS Transport with Custom AWS URL in Wolverine (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure the Amazon SQS transport in Wolverine using custom configuration values such as ServiceURL, which can point to a given SQS endpoint. The example demonstrates setting SQS-specific settings via the UseAmazonSqsTransport delegate and reads parameters from builder.Configuration. It maintains the ability to auto-provision and purge SQS queues. Dependencies include WolverineFx.AmazonSqs and any configuration sources for AWS parameters. The host is started after building with the given configuration.
