TITLE: Disabling Rabbit MQ System Request/Reply Queues in Wolverine C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to disable Wolverine's automatic creation of system reply queues in Rabbit MQ, which is useful when broker permissions are insufficient. The .DisableSystemRequestReplyQueueDeclaration() option prevents issues during deployment or local testing in restricted environments, but also disables request/reply support through Rabbit MQ in Wolverine. The configuration uses a URI schema, and sets queue options for 'incoming2'. Requires WolverineFX.RabbitMQ and a Rabbit MQ broker accessible via URI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/wolverine/blob/main/docs/guide/messaging/transports/rabbitmq/index.md#_snippet_4

