TITLE: Implementing Request Timing Middleware in Wolverine HTTP (C#)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a `StopwatchMiddleware` class for Wolverine HTTP endpoints. It uses a `Stopwatch` instance, starting it in the `Before` method (executed before the endpoint handler) and stopping it in the `Finally` method (executed after the handler, regardless of success or failure). The `Finally` method logs the request path and duration using injected `ILogger` and `HttpContext`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jasperfx/wolverine/blob/main/docs/guide/http/middleware.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
public class StopwatchMiddleware
{
    private readonly Stopwatch _stopwatch = new();

    public void Before()
    {
        _stopwatch.Start();
    }

    public void Finally(ILogger logger, HttpContext context)
    {
        _stopwatch.Stop();
        logger.LogDebug("Request for route {Route} ran in {Duration} milliseconds",
            context.Request.Path, _stopwatch.ElapsedMilliseconds);
    }
}
```

